# Secure 3-Tier Architecture on AWS using Terraform

# Overview

This project provisions a *secure, production-inspired 3-tier architecture* on AWS using Terraform.

It demonstrates best practices in:

* Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
* Network isolation
* Layered security design
* Remote state management

# Architecture

The infrastructure is divided into three logical tiers:

* *Web Tier (Public Subnet)*
  Handles incoming HTTP requests from users

* *App Tier (Private Subnet)*
  Processes business logic and application workflows

* *DB Tier (Private Subnet)*
  Stores application data securely

# Technologies Used

* Terraform
* AWS (VPC, EC2, Security Group, NAT Gateway, Internet Gateway, Route Tables)
* S3 (Remote State Backend)
* DynamoDB (State Locking)

# Architecture Diagram

Internet
   │
   ▼
Internet Gateway
   │
Public Subnet (Web Tier EC2)
   │
Private Subnet (App Tier EC2)
   │
Private Subnet (DB Tier EC2)

# Security Design

This project follows *defense-in-depth principles*:

* *Public access restricted to Web tier only*
* *App tier accepts traffic only from Web tier*
* *DB tier accepts traffic only from App tier*
* *Private subnets have no direct internet access*
* *NAT Gateway enables outbound-only internet for private resources*

# Project Structure

terraform-3tier-aws/
│
├── main.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
├── provider.tf
│
└── terraform.tfvars

# Terraform Backend

Remote state is configured using:

* *S3 Bucket* → Stores Terraform state
* *DynamoDB Table* → Prevents concurrent modifications (state locking)

# Getting Started

# 1. Clone the Repository

bash
git clone git@github.com:damilola-ajayi04/x3-tier.git
cd x3-tier


# 2. Initialize Terraform

bash
terraform init


# 3. Preview Infrastructure

bash
terraform plan


# 4. Deploy

bash
terraform apply

# Important Notes

* This project uses a *single AZ (for demo purposes)*

# Improvements (Next Steps if required)

* Multi-AZ deployment for high availability

# Key Learnings

* How to design a secure 3-tier architecture
* Terraform resource dependencies and structure
* AWS networking fundamentals (VPC, subnets, routing)
* Secure infrastructure design principles
